definitions.definition: A natural or inherent impulse or behaviour .
examples: Many animals fear fire by instinct .

definitions.definition: An intuitive reaction not based on rational conscious thought.
examples: an instinct for order; to be modest by instinct
Debbie's instinct was to distrust John.

main_definition: A natural or inherent impulse or behaviour .
secondary_definitions: An intuitive reaction not based on rational conscious thought.
